5.5.1.2 The effects of this technology are:
- 7 gelatinization of the starchy portion of the mixture with minimal quantities of water;
- 7 inactivation of lectins and reduction of trypsin inhibitor activity;
- 7 a reduction in the quantities of water needed for preparation of the food;
- 7 flavour development.

6.1.1 The selection of raw materials and ingredients for the formulation of Formulated Complementary Foods for Older Infants and Young Children should be made having regard to the provisions in Sections 4 and 5 and taking into account the following aspects:
- 7 nutrient content of the local diet;
- 7 dietary habits and infant feeding practices;
- 7 other socio-economic aspects as determined by the national authorities dealing with nutrition;
- 7 availability and quality of raw materials and ingredients.
